How to run locally (quick)

1. Start MySQL and backend:

    Option A (docker-compose): docker-compose up --build

    Option B (locally): Run MySQL locally, set DATABASE_URI in .env, then in backend/:

    python -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate

    pip install -r requirements.txt

    flask db init && flask db migrate && flask db upgrade (or create tables from SQL)

    python app.py

2. Start frontend:

    cd frontend

    npm install

    npm start

3. Visit:

    Frontend: http://localhost:3000

    Backend API: http://localhost:5000/api/pizzas